Remote Learning DROP OFF information:

Remote Learning Packets need to be dropped off during the following times in the High School circle drive.
• Seniors - Monday, May 11, 2020 - 9:00 am – 11:00 am
• PreK - 11th Grade - Tuesday, May 26, 2020 – 9:00 am – 11:00 am

GS students need to return their completed work that they picked up on May 4th.

JH and HS students need to turn in any completed homework that has not been sent to their teachers through remind or email.

Students through 8th grade who do not turn in their completed work by May 26th will earn an incomplete grade for 4th quarter.

If you have any library books or owe any fees, please make sure they are turned in before your drop off date.

School Lunches will continue to be served Monday, Wednesday, and Friday through May 27th. (Excluding Memorial Day) If you have signed up for lunches, please make sure you come and get it.

post_text:
Our high school secretary, Becky Casey, is retiring after this school year. Becky has been serving Ramsey School District for 29 years! Due to the pandemic we had to celebrate Becky a little differently than we normally do for our retirees. Today Becky was presented with a new bench and a basket of goodies to enjoy.

Becky’s smile and kindness will certainly be missed at school, but we are so happy that she is able to retire and will be able to do all the things she enjoys.

Thank you Becky for your dedication to our school district! Congratulations on your retirement! 🧡🖤

Please remember to stay in your car and pull up to the table marked with your student’s grade level. Those who are receiving lunches will get their folder at their normal pick up or delivery time.

GS students need to return their folder that they received on April 2nd with their completed work in the folder. The classroom teacher will hand them a new folder with a new choice board and learning activities for another two weeks.

The JH and HS students need to turn in the packets that they were given on the last day they attended school as well as any completed homework that has not been sent to their teachers through remind or email.

Parents who have not joined the Remind app please do ASAP.

If you have any questions, please contact your building principal.

shared_text:
Regional Office of Education #3
March 30 at 4:24 PM ·

For those who need to hear it....

EDUCATION TEAM! Yes, YOU! Teachers, paras, food service, custodians, secretaries, bookkeepers, bus drivers, counselors, therapists, administrators - all ye who work in and with the schools! Take note: YOU ARE AWESOME!! Look at what you've achieved this month! Holy mokes! Who else could have done all this? I'll tell you who - NO ONE!! Way to go team!! You hit the ground running and never let up!

Remote learning? Yes, we can do this. We will continue to do this. We will feed the children, care for the children, and yes, even teach the children. We will take care of our personal families and our school family and our student families. Why? Cuz it's what we do.

We'll help you. We'll all help each other. THIS IS OUR TIME TO SHINE IN EDUCATION!! Look at us go! We can do this - together!! Keep calm, wash your hands, and HERE WE GO!!!!

And I wouldn't want to do it with anyone else. 😀❤️

post_text:
From Kayla Tipsword, yearbook sponsor.....

Hello All RHS Students, Parents, and Guardians,
The COVID-19 virus has drastically changed our lives over the last couple weeks. This has also affected our school year as well. Because of this change, the RHS Yearbook Staff is in need of your help. We would love to document some of your home memories during this time. We would like to be able to picture as many students as possible going about their daily lives: watching TV, playing a game with the family, hanging out with siblings and parents, cooking, baking, going for a walk, etc. Although this is not the school we dreamed of, we still want our students to have the best yearbook possible! You are welcome to email them to kwilhelm@ramseycusd.org or have your students send them to her using Remind. Also, we would love some funny sibling pictures for any siblings that are both in high school for our sibling page. Thanks in advance for your help!
Ramsey High School Yearbook Rampage
text:
From Kayla Tipsword, yearbook sponsor.....

Hello All RHS Students, Parents, and Guardians,
The COVID-19 virus has drastically changed our lives over the last couple weeks. This has also affected our school year as well. Because of this change, the RHS Yearbook Staff is in need of your help. We would love to document some of your home memories during this time. We would like to be able to picture as many students as possible going about their daily lives: watching TV, playing a game with the family, hanging out with siblings and parents, cooking, baking, going for a walk, etc. Although this is not the school we dreamed of, we still want our students to have the best yearbook possible! You are welcome to email them to kwilhelm@ramseycusd.org or have your students send them to her using Remind. Also, we would love some funny sibling pictures for any siblings that are both in high school for our sibling page. Thanks in advance for your help!

post_text: Sixth grade students have been finding the surface area of rectangular prisms and other 3-dimensional objects. post_text: Today, a bus could not make it up a hill while in route to school. There were 16 students on the bus. No students were injured. All student's and the driver waited on the warm bus for another bus to arrive. Student's exited one bus and got on another and were transported to school safely. Thank you to everyone who helped with the transition. If you have any questions, please contact the school.
text: Today, a bus could not make it up a hill while in route to school. There were 16 students on the bus. No students were injured. All student's and the driver waited on the warm bus for another bus to arrive. Student's exited one bus and got on another and were transported to school safely. Thank you to everyone who helped with the transition. If you have any questions, please contact the school.

post_text: On Friday, December 13, the RHS juniors and sophomores participated in a presentation from ISAC (Illinois Student Assistance Commission) on college and career information. Students heard information regarding different college degrees and programs to many career opportunities. This was a great experience for students to start the exploration process of their future.
